    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--1\"><p><i>7th-level Psi Warrior feature</i></p><p>You have mastered new ways to use your telekinetic abilities, detailed below.</p><ul class=\"rd__list rd__list-hang-notitle\"><li class=\"rd__li \"><p class=\"rd__p-list-item\" data-roll-name-ancestor=\"Psi-Powered Leap.\"><span class=\"bold rd__list-item-name\">Psi-Powered Leap.</span> As a bonus action, you can propel your body with your mind. You gain a flying speed equal to twice your walking speed until the end of the current turn. Once you take this bonus action, you can't do so again until you finish a short or long rest, unless you expend a Psionic Energy die to take it again.</p></li><li class=\"rd__li \"><p class=\"rd__p-list-item\" data-roll-name-ancestor=\"Telekinetic Thrust.\"><span class=\"bold rd__list-item-name\">Telekinetic Thrust.</span> When you deal damage to a target with your Psionic Strike, you can force the target to make a Strength saving throw against a DC equal to 8 + your proficiency bonus + your Intelligence modifier. If the save fails, you can knock the target &amp;Reference[condition=prone] or move it up to 10 feet in any direction horizontally.</p></li></ul></div>",
